ActsAsReadonly
==============

acts_as_readonly is an ActiveRecord plugin that makes a model readonly, preventing its attributes from being set and calling methods like save, create, and destroy on it.

This plugin is useful for working with risky, legacy or third party database data is only being viewed.

Example
=======

class MyModel < ActiveRecord::Base
  acts_as_readonly
end

Installation
=======
$ ./script/plugin install git@github.com:kevincolyar/acts_as_readonly.git



